	<div class="flex-container">
		<p data-scroll class = "item">galdrastrákur is a "miniature" horror game where player must solve puzzles during the day so that they can escape “the witch” at night</p>
 	 </div>
   <div class="flex-container">
		<p data-scroll class = "item">Based on Icelandic Folk Song “Bium bium bambalo,” it's setting and style is based on Icelandic</p>
 	 </div>
   
   <div class="flex-container">
		<p data-scroll class = "item">Based on Icelandic Folk Song “Bium bium bambalo,” it's setting and style is based on Icelandic</p>
 	 </div>
	
	<div class="flex-box">
		<img src = "img/project 03/Untitled_Artwork 20.png" id = "ogbox" data-scroll>
	</div>
	
	<div class="flex-container">
		<p data-scroll class = "item">My initial idea for the Cornell box was actually based on my childhood, specifically with elements like the "piano" and the "deer." However, I wanted the project to have more of a "storyline" rather than just being an interactive experience. It ended up becoming a hybrid of the initial concept and the Courage the Cowardly Dog episode. Consequently, the project ended up taking an almost surrealist tone. I specifically wanted to play with the idea of a "TV Box" when considering what exactly a Cornell box is.</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="flex-container">
		<h5 data-scroll>Interaction Wireframe</h5>
	</div>
	
